{"title_page": "Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix", "text_new": "{{short description|Portuguese association football player}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2016}}\n{{Portuguese name|F\u00e9lix|Sequeira}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n|name = Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix\n|image = Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix 2019.jpg\n|image_size = \n|caption = F\u00e9lix with [[Atl\u00e9tico Madrid]] in 2019\n|fullname = Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix Sequeira<ref>{{cite web|url=http://actas.rfef.es/actas/RFEF_CmpActa1?cod_primaria=1000144&CodActa=60726|title=Acta del Partido celebrado el 01 de marzo de 2020, en Barcelona|trans-title=Minutes of the Match held on 1 March 2020, in Barcelona|publisher=Royal Spanish Football Federation|access-date=2 March 2020|language=Spanish}}</ref>\n|birth_date = {{birth date and age|1999|11|10|df=y}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/player/_/id/276350/joao-felix|title=Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix|publisher=ESPN|access-date=2 March 2020}}</ref>\n|birth_place = [[Viseu]], Portugal\n|height = 1.81 m<ref>{{cite web|url=https://en.atleticodemadrid.com/jugadores/jo-o-felix-2019-2020-2|title=Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix|publisher=Atl\u00e9tico Madrid|access-date=2 March 2020}}</ref>\n|position = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]]\n|currentclub = [[Atl\u00e9tico Madrid]]\n|clubnumber = 7\n|youthyears1 = 2007\u20132008\n|youthclubs1 = Os Pestinhas\n|youthyears2 = 2008\u20132015\n|youthclubs2 = [[FC Porto|Porto]]\n|youthyears3 = 2014\u20132015\n|youthclubs3 = \u2192 [[Padroense F.C.|Padroense]] (loan)\n|youthyears4 = 2015\u20132018\n|youthclubs4 = [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]]\n|years1 = 2016\u20132018\n|clubs1 = [[S.L. Benfica B|Benfica B]]\n|caps1 = 30\n|goals1 = 7\n|years2 = 2018\u20132019\n|clubs2 = [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]]\n|caps2 = 26\n|goals2 = 15\n|years3 = 2019\u2013\n|clubs3 = [[Atl\u00e9tico Madrid]]\n|caps3 = 20\n|goals3 = 4\n|nationalyears1 = 2017\n|nationalteam1 = [[Portugal national under-18 football team|Portugal U18]]\n|nationalcaps1 = 2\n|nationalgoals1 = 2\n|nationalyears2 = 2018\n|nationalteam2 = [[Portugal national under-19 football team|Portugal U19]]\n|nationalcaps2 = 2\n|nationalgoals2 = 0\n|nationalyears3 = 2017\u2013\n|nationalteam3 = [[Portugal national under-21 football team|Portugal U21]]\n|nationalcaps3 = 10\n|nationalgoals3 = 4\n|nationalyears4 = 2019\u2013\n|nationalteam4 = [[Portugal national football team|Portugal]]\n|nationalcaps4 = 5\n|nationalgoals4 = 0\n|club-update = 17:16, 7 March 2020 (UTC)\n|nationalteam-update = 00:24, 2 March 2020 (UTC)\n|medaltemplates = {{MedalSport|Men's [[Association football|football]]}}\n{{medalCountry|[[Portugal national football team|Portugal]]}}\n{{medalCompetition|[[UEFA Nations League]]}}\n{{medal|Winner|[[2019 UEFA Nations League Finals|2019 Portugal]]|}}\n}}\n'''Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix Sequeira''' ({{IPA-pt|\u0292u\u02c8\u0250\u0303w \u02c8f\u025bliks|}};{{refn|group=n|Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix himself pronounces his name as {{IPA-pt|-liks|}},<ref name=pron>{{cite media|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=OhOKReTdYLM&t=60|title=Entrevista Campe\u00e3o37 \u2013 Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix|date=2019-05-24|last=|first=|type=|language=|publisher=[[S.L. Benfica]]|time=60 seconds|via=[[YouTube]]}}</ref> but this name is also commonly pronounced {{IPA-pt|-li\u0283|}}.<ref name=pron/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://ciberduvidas.iscte-iul.pt/aberturas/tipos-de-texto-o-nome-felix-os-lusismos-do-ingles-o-escritor-nelson-rodrigues-e-a-diversidade-lingui/2413|title=Tipos de texto, o (sempre mal dito) nome F\u00e9lix, 10 lusismos do ingl\u00eas, e algumas das express\u00f5es mais saborosas de Nelson Rodrigues|date=4 February 2019|website=Ciberd\u00favidas da L\u00edngua Portuguesa|publisher=[[ISCTE \u2013 University Institute of Lisbon]]|language=pt|trans-title=Types of text, the (always badly spelt) ''F\u00e9lix'' name, 10 English ''lusismos'', and some of the tastiest expressions of Nelson Rodrigues|access-date=5 March 2019}}</ref>}} born 10 November 1999) is a Portuguese professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]] for Spanish [[La Liga]] club [[Atl\u00e9tico Madrid]] and the [[Portugal national football team|Portugal national team]]. He is known for his speed, finishing, technique and his [[Dribbling#Association football|dribbling]] and he can also play as a [[Midfielder#Winger|winger]] or an [[Midfielder#Attacking midfielder|attacking midfielder]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://bleacherreport.com/articles/2858128-matthijs-de-ligt-joao-felix-jadon-sancho-on-20-man-2019-golden-boy-shortlist |title=Matthijs de Ligt, Joao Felix, Jadon Sancho on 20-Man 2019 Golden Boy Shortlist |publisher=Bleacher Report |last1=Jones |first1=Matt |date=15 October 2019 |accessdate=8 March 2020 }}</ref><ref name=\"en.as.com\">{{cite web |url=https://en.as.com/en/2019/06/18/football/1560852116_870651.html |title=Tactical analysis of Joao F\u00e9lix: a difference-making transfer |publisher=AS |last1=Sill\u00e9s |first1=Javier |date=18 June 2019 |accessdate=8 March 2020 }}</ref>\n\nF\u00e9lix initially trained at [[FC Porto|Porto]]'s youth ranks before moving to rivals [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]] in 2015. He began playing for the latter's [[S.L. Benfica B|reserve team]] a year later and was promoted to the first-team in 2018, making his professional debut at age 18. He then starred as a goalscorer and helped Benfica win the [[2018\u201319 Primeira Liga|league title]] in [[2018\u201319 S.L. Benfica season|his first and only season with them]], and was awarded Primeira Liga's Best Young Player of the Year and the [[Golden Boy (award)|Golden Boy]] award.<ref name=\"GoldenBoy\">{{cite web |url=https://www.tuttosport.com/news/calcio/golden-boy/2019/11/27-63853409/il_profilo_del_golden_boy_joo_flix_il_predestinato/|title=Il profilo del Golden Boy Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix: il predestinato|trans-title=The profile of the Golden Boy Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix: the predestined|date=27 November 2019 |publisher=Tuttosport|language=it|accessdate=27 November 2019}}</ref> Internationally, he became the youngest ever player to score a [[hat-trick]] in the [[UEFA Europa League]], aged 19.\n\nF\u00e9lix's performances sparked the interest of several European clubs, with Atl\u00e9tico Madrid signing him in 2019 for a club-record transfer worth \u20ac126&nbsp;million (\u00a3113&nbsp;million), the [[List of most expensive association football transfers|fourth-most expensive football transfer]], the second-most ever paid for a teenager and the highest fee for a Portuguese player leaving the domestic league. Shortly after, F\u00e9lix was listed among the shortlist for the [[Ballon d'Or]] and finished third for the [[Kopa Trophy]] in 2019.<ref name=\"BallonDOr\">{{cite news |url=https://www.francefootball.fr/diaporama/Le-classement-complet-du-ballon-d-or-france-football-2019/7777/#30|title=The complete ranking of the Ballon d'Or France Football 2019 |newspaper=France Football |date=2 December 2019 |accessdate=9 December 2019}}</ref>\n\nAfter being [[Cap (sport)|capped]] for Portugal's youth teams at [[Portugal national under-18 football team|under-18]], [[Portugal national under-19 football team|under-19]] and [[Portugal national under-21 football team|under-21]] levels, F\u00e9lix made his senior debut in the semi-finals of the [[2019 UEFA Nations League Finals]], won by Portugal on home soil.\n\n==Club career==\n===Early career===\nBorn in [[Viseu]],<ref name=\"Soccerway\"/> F\u00e9lix started playing football at Os Pestinhas in 2007 before joining the youth ranks of [[FC Porto]] a year later, aged eight.<ref name=DiarioNoticias>{{cite news |url=https://www.dn.pt/desportos/benfica-segura-joao-felix-o-miudo-franzino-que-nao-foi-aproveitado-pelo-fc-porto-10114601.html |title=Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix, o mi\u00fado franzino que o FC Porto n\u00e3o aproveitou |trans-title=Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix, the skinny kid that Porto did not take advantage of |work=Di\u00e1rio de Not\u00edcias |language=Portuguese |last1=Fernandes |first1=Nuno |date=5 November 2018 |accessdate=8 March 2020 }}</ref> After F\u00e9lix moved to [[Porto]], he faced some challenges such as extensive schedules that included daily shuttle hours between Viseu and Porto.<ref name=lb>{{cite web|title=Hist\u00f3ria da inf\u00e2ncia do Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix e fatos incont\u00e1veis de biografia|trans-title=Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix's childhood story and countless facts of biography|url=https://lifebogger.com/pt/joao-felix-hist%C3%B3ria-de-inf%C3%A2ncia-mais-fatos-de-biografia-n%C3%A3o-revelada/|access-date=4 May 2019|website=Life Blogger|date=4 May 2019|language=pt}}</ref>{{Better source|reason=It does not seem to be a reliable source.|date=September 2019}} He moved to his parents' house to be near Porto's training grounds and, later, he wanted to quit football due to missing his parents, but his father convinced him on pursuing his career.<ref name=lb/> F\u00e9lix was released by Porto in 2014 because of his slight frame and moved on to [[Lisbon]] rivals [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]] in 2015, aged 15, after a season-long loan at [[Padroense F.C.|Padroense]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Azevedo|first=Pedro Miguel|title=Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix, o magricela que escapou ao FC Porto e brilha no Benfica|trans-title=Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix, the scrawny kid who slipped from FC Porto and shines for Benfica|url=https://www.ojogo.pt/futebol/1a-liga/benfica/noticias/interior/joao-felix-o-magricela-que-escapou-ao-fc-porto-e-brilha-no-benfica-6245594.html|access-date=1 February 2018|newspaper=[[O Jogo]]|date=26 April 2017|language=pt}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Paulo Ribeiro|first=Jo\u00e3o|date=19 June 2019|title=Presidente do Padroense orgulhoso pelo contributo do clube no crescimento de F\u00e9lix|trans-title=Padroense president proud of the club's contribution to the growth of Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix|url=https://rr.sapo.pt/2019/06/19/benfica/presidente-do-padroense-orgulhoso-pelo-contributo-do-clube-no-crescimento-de-felix/noticia/155267/|language=pt|work=[[R\u00e1dio Renascen\u00e7a]]|access-date=11 September 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Smith|first=Roy|author-link=Rory Smith (journalist)|date=12 September 2019|title=Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix Is in a Hurry. So Is Everyone Else.|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/09/12/sports/joao-felix-atletico-madrid.html|newspaper=[[The New York Times]]|access-date=12 September 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Benfica===\n{{quote box\n| quote = \"They've already called him my heir or the new Kaka. To be honest, Felix is just Felix. He has an extraordinary understanding of the game and the rare ability to know where to be in front of goal.\"\n| source = \u2014 [[Rui Costa]] on F\u00e9lix's playing style<ref name=\"davis\">{{cite news|last=Davis|first=Matt|title=Joao Felix: The Benfica wonderkid who has been called the most exciting player since Cristiano Ronaldo|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/48385500|access-date=27 May 2019|work=BBC Sport|date=26 May 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|date=22 March 2019|url=https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-nos/benfica/detalhe/rui-costa-sobre-joao-felix-ha-jogadores-que-nao-conseguimos-reter-em-portugal|title=Rui Costa sobre Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix: \"H\u00e1 jogadores que n\u00e3o conseguimos reter em Portugal\"|newspaper=[[Record (newspaper)|Record]]}}</ref>\n| align = right\n| width = 28%\n}}\nF\u00e9lix debuted professionally at the age of 16 for Benfica's [[S.L. Benfica B|reserve team]] in [[LigaPro]] on 17 September 2016, coming on as an 83rd-minute substitute for [[Aur\u00e9lio Buta]] in a goalless draw at [[S.C. Freamunde|Freamunde]]. In doing so, he became the youngest player to debut for Benfica B.<ref>{{cite news|last=Ponte|first=Pedro|date=17 September 2016|title=Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix \u00e9 o mais novo de sempre a jogar pelo Benfica B|trans-title=Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix is the youngest ever to play for Benfica B|url=http://www.record.xl.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-nos/benfica/detalhe/joao-felix-e-o-mais-novo-de-sempre-a-jogar-pela-benfica-b.html|language=pt|newspaper=Record|access-date=18 June 2019}}</ref> He played 13 matches and scored three goals over [[2016\u201317 LigaPro|the season]], the first being a consolation in a 2\u20131 loss to his hometown team [[Acad\u00e9mico de Viseu F.C.|Acad\u00e9mico de Viseu]] on 15 February 2017.<ref>{{cite news|title=Benfica B perde com o Acad\u00e9mico em Viseu|trans-title=Benfica B lose to Acad\u00e9mico in Viseu|url=http://www.maisfutebol.iol.pt/academico-viseu/15-02-2017/ii-liga-benfica-b-procura-3-vitoria-seguida-em-casa-do-ac-viseu|access-date=1 February 2018|work=Maisfutebol|date=15 February 2017|language=pt}}</ref> Later, on 30 January 2018, he scored a [[hat-trick]] in a 5\u20130 home win over [[F.C. Famalic\u00e3o|Famalic\u00e3o]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix marca tr\u00eas golos na goleada do Benfica B ao Famalic\u00e3o|trans-title=Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix scores three goals in Benfica B's thrashing of Famalic\u00e3o|url=https://www.dn.pt/desporto/benfica/interior/joao-felix-marca-tres-golos-na-goleada-do-benfica-b-ao-famalicao-9085800.html|access-date=1 February 2018|newspaper=[[Di\u00e1rio de Not\u00edcias]]|date=30 January 2018|language=pt}}</ref> During that season, F\u00e9lix played in the [[2016\u201317 UEFA Youth League]], in which he was a key part of Benfica reaching the final of the competition, lost to [[FC Red Bull Salzburg|Red Bull Salzburg]] (2\u20131); he scored six goals in the tournament.{{citation needed|date=March 2020}}\n\nF\u00e9lix was then promoted to Benfica's first team for the [[2018\u201319 S.L. Benfica season|2018\u201319 season]], making his debut in a 2\u20130 [[Primeira Liga]] win at [[Boavista F.C.|Boavista]] on 18 August. A week later, he scored his first Primeira Liga goal, thus becoming the youngest player to score in the [[Derby de Lisboa|Lisbon derby]], which ended in a 1\u20131 tie.<ref>{{cite news|title=Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix: \"I shivered\"|url=https://www.slbenfica.pt/en-us/agora/noticias/2018-2019/08/25/joao-felix-declaracoes-futebol-benfica-sporting-derbi-3-jornada-liga-nos|access-date=25 August 2018|publisher=[[S.L. Benfica]]|date=25 August 2018}}</ref> On 16 January 2019, he scored the qualifying goal against [[Vit\u00f3ria S.C.|Vit\u00f3ria de Guimar\u00e3es]] in the [[Ta\u00e7a de Portugal|Portuguese Cup]] quarter-finals.<ref>{{cite news|date=15 January 2019|title=Golo de Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix apura Benfica para as meias-finais da Ta\u00e7a de Portugal|trans-title=F\u00e9lix's goal qualifies Benfica to the Portuguese Cup semi-finals|url=https://24.sapo.pt/desporto/artigos/golo-de-joao-felix-apura-benfica-para-as-meias-finais-da-taca-de-portugal|language=pt|work=[[SAPO (company)|SAPO]] Desporto|access-date=8 February 2019}}</ref> After [[Bruno Lage]] took over as coach of Benfica, his first decision was to use F\u00e9lix more regularly, partnering him with [[Haris Seferovi\u0107]] in the attack.<ref>{{cite news|last=Oliveira|first=Diogo Cardoso|date=23 May 2019|title=A primeira decis\u00e3o de Lage: \"Meter o mi\u00fado Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix a jogar\"|trans-title=Lage's first decision: \"To put the kid Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix playing\"|url=https://www.publico.pt/2019/05/23/desporto/noticia/lage-recorda-primeira-decisao-treinador-meter-miudo-joao-felix-jogar-1873832|language=pt|newspaper=[[P\u00fablico (Portugal)|P\u00fablico]]|access-date=5 July 2019}}</ref> Later on, F\u00e9lix was praised for his performance in a 4\u20132 away win over [[Sporting CP]] in the league on 3 February,<ref name=\"paraeles\">{{cite news|last=Martins|first=Andr\u00e9 Cruz|date=6 February 2019|title=Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix, uma mistura de Rui Costa e Jo\u00e3o Pinto com tra\u00e7os de Cruyff|trans-title=Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix, a mixture of Rui Costa and Jo\u00e3o Pinto with Cruyff traits|url=https://www.paraeles.pt/desporto/joao-felix-uma-mistura-de-rui-costa-e-joao-pinto-com-tracos-de-cruyff/|language=pt|work=Para Eles|access-date=14 February 2019}}</ref> subsequently sparking interest from several European clubs.<ref>{{cite news|date=5 February 2019|title=Cl\u00e1usula de rescis\u00e3o de Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix pode subir|trans-title=Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix's release clause may go up|url=https://www.abola.pt/Clubes/Noticias/Ver/772041/40|url-status=dead|language=pt|newspaper=[[A Bola]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190205160452/https://abola.pt/Clubes/Noticias/Ver/772041/40/|archive-date=5 February 2019|access-date=14 February 2019}}</ref> A month later, he scored the equaliser in a 2\u20131 away win over Porto in the league.<ref>{{cite news|date=17 March 2019|title=Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix explica festejo de joelhos no Drag\u00e3o|trans-title=Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix explains celebration on his knees at Drag\u00e3o|url=https://maisfutebol.iol.pt/benfica/liga/joao-felix-explica-festejo-de-joelhos-no-dragao|language=pt|work=Maisfutebol|access-date=3 July 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn 11 April 2019, F\u00e9lix scored a hat-trick in a 4\u20132 [[UEFA Europa League]] win over [[Eintracht Frankfurt]]. In doing so, he became the youngest ever player (aged 19 years and 152 days) to score a hat-trick in the competition, breaking [[Marko Pjaca]]'s record by 67 days.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/47903362|title=Europa League Roundup: Joao Felix hat-trick; English refs award three pens and a red|work=[[BBC Sport]]|date=11 April 2019|access-date=12 April 2019}}</ref> F\u00e9lix finished his first season with 20 goals for his team, including one on the final day of the league campaign, in a 4\u20131 win over [[C.D. Santa Clara|Santa Clara]] to seal the title;<ref>{{cite news|title=Benfica-Santa Clara: Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix chega aos 20 golos pela equipa principal|trans-title=Benfica-Santa Clara: Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix reaches 20 goals for the first team|url=https://www.ojogo.pt/futebol/1a-liga/benfica/noticias/interior/benfica-santa-clara-joao-felix-chega-aos-20-golos-pela-equipa-principal-10914534.html|access-date=27 May 2019|newspaper=O Jogo|date=18 May 2019|language=pt}}</ref> his 15 league goals put him joint-fourth for the season.<ref>{{cite news|title=Goleadores: Seferovi\u0107 \u00e9 o melhor marcador da Liga|trans-title=Goalscorers: Haris Seferovi\u0107 is the top scorer in the League|url=https://maisfutebol.iol.pt/benfica/campeao/goleadores-seferovic-e-o-melhor-marcador-da-liga|access-date=27 May 2019|work=Maisfutebol|date=18 May 2019|language=pt}}</ref> Across Europe's seven best leagues, he ranked second among teenagers for goals and assists, behind [[Kai Havertz]] and [[Jadon Sancho]], respectively.<ref name=\"davis\"/>\n\n===Atl\u00e9tico Madrid===\nOn 3 July 2019, F\u00e9lix signed a seven-year contract with Spanish club [[Atl\u00e9tico Madrid]] for a transfer fee of \u20ac126&nbsp;million (\u00a3113&nbsp;million), the [[List of most expensive association football transfers|third highest ever paid in football]]<ref>{{cite news|date=3 July 2019|title=Atl\u00e9tico Madrid sign Benfica teenager Jo\u00e3o Felix for fee of \u20ac126m|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2019/jul/03/atletico-madrid-sign-benfica-teenager-joao-felix-for-fee-of-126m|newspaper=[[The Guardian]]|agency=[[Reuters]]|access-date=17 July 2019}}</ref> (Benfica's biggest transfer and Atl\u00e9tico's most expensive signing) as well as the second highest for a teenager (after [[Kylian Mbapp\u00e9]]), with the [[La Liga]] club initially paying \u20ac30&nbsp;million and the rest \u20ac96&nbsp;million via [[wiktionary:installment|installment]]s, thus surpassing F\u00e9lix's \u20ac120&nbsp;million [[release clause]], and with Benfica paying \u20ac12&nbsp;million in mediation services.<ref>{{cite news|date=3 July 2019|title=Comunicado \u00e0 CMVM|trans-title=Announcement to CMVM|url=https://www.slbenfica.pt/pt-pt/agora/noticias/2019/07/03/futebol-benfica-comunicado-cmvm-joao-felix-atletico-de-madrid|language=pt|publisher=S.L. Benfica|access-date=3 July 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Garcia|first=Adriana|date=3 July 2019|title=Atletico pay \u20ac126m to sign 'New Ronaldo' Felix|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/soccer-transfers/story/3877518/atletico-pay-126m-to-sign-new-ronaldo-felix|publisher=[[ESPN]]|access-date=3 July 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/48859847|title=Joao Felix: Atletico Madrid sign forward from Benfica for \u00a3113m|work=BBC Sport|date=3 July 2019|access-date=4 July 2019}}</ref> Upon his arrival to the club he was handed the number 7 shirt, previously worn by [[Antoine Griezmann]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix apresentado em direto pelo Atl\u00e9tico de Madrid|url=https://www.impala.pt/desporto/joao-felix-atletico-madrid/|access-date=8 July 2019|work=Impala|date=8 July 2019|language=pt}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix no At. Madrid por sete temporadas|url=https://www.dn.pt/desportos/interior/oficial-joao-felix-no-atletico-de-madrid-11056397.html|work=Di\u00e1rio de Not\u00edcias|date=8 July 2019|language=pt}}</ref>\n\n[[File:20191002SR.jpg|thumb|upright|F\u00e9lix playing for [[Atl\u00e9tico Madrid]] in a away [[2019\u201320 UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] match against [[Lokomotiv Moscow]].]]\nF\u00e9lix made his competitive debut on 19 August, in a 1\u20130 victory over [[Getafe CF|Getafe]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.marca.com/en/football/spanish-football/cronica/2019/08/19/5d59d500268e3e1b448b45c2.html|title=Atletico Madrid start the season in typical fashion|website=MARCA|date=19 August 2019}}</ref> Despite not scoring a goal, he managed to get a penalty for Atl\u00e9tico after being fouled, a penalty that [[\u00c1lvaro Morata]] failed to convert.<ref>{{cite news|title=A jogada de Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix de que todos falam|url=https://pt.besoccer.com/noticia/a-jogada-de-joao-felix-de-que-todos-falam-581512|work=BeSoccer|date=19 August 2019|language=pt}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|date=19 August 2019|title=S\u00f3 com pen\u00e1lti o Getafe travou jogada genial de F\u00e9lix|url=https://www.abola.pt/nnh/Noticias/Ver/802008|url-status=live|language=pt|newspaper=A Bola|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190818235517/https://www.abola.pt/nnh/Noticias/Ver/802008|archive-date=18 August 2018|access-date=18 August 2019}}</ref> On 25 August, F\u00e9lix provided an assist for [[Vitolo (footballer, born 1989)|Vitolo]] in a 1\u20130 away win over against [[CD Legan\u00e9s]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://observador.pt/2019/08/25/ainda-sem-golos-mas-com-assistencia-atl-madrid-bate-leganes-com-joao-felix-a-assistir-para-o-golo-da-vitoria/ |title=Ainda sem golos mas com assist\u00eancia: Atl. Madrid bate Legan\u00e9s com Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix a assistir para o golo da vit\u00f3ria|website=Observador|date=23 August 2019 |accessdate=23 August 2019}}</ref> He scored his first La Liga goal on 1 September, in a 3\u20132 victory over [[SD Eibar|Eibar]]; he was later substituted in the 84th minute by [[Thomas Partey]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://trivela.com.br/joao-felix-fez-seu-primeiro-gol-oficial-pelo-atletico-e-deu-inicio-a-virada-contra-o-eibar/|title=Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix fez seu primeiro gol oficial pelo Atl\u00e9tico e deu in\u00edcio \u00e0 virada contra o Eibar|website=Trivela|date=1 September 2019|last=Bonsanti|first=Bruno}}</ref> On 1 October, F\u00e9lix scored his first [[2019\u201320 UEFA Champions League|UEFA Champions League]] goal and set up another goal in a 2-1 away victory against [[Lokomotiv Moscow]], becoming in the process, the youngest goalscorer for Atletico Madrid in this competition at 19 years old.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sol.sapo.pt/artigo/672943/joao-felix-estreia-se-a-marcar-na-liga-dos-campeoes-e-faz-historia-ao-quebrar-recorde-video|title=Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix estreia-se a marcar na Liga dos Campe\u00f5es e faz hist\u00f3ria ao quebrar recorde|website=Jornal SOL|date=1 October 2019}}</ref> On 19 October, F\u00e9lix suffered an ankle injury against [[Valencia CF|Valencia]], after a rash challenge by [[Dani Parejo]], leading his team to be down with 10-men, since his coach [[Diego Simeone]] had made all the substitutions.<ref>{{cite_web|url=https://www.cmjornal.pt/desporto/futebol/detalhe/joao-felix-lesionou-se-com-gravidade-no-jogo-contra-o-valencia|title=Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix lesionou-se com gravidade no jogo contra o valencia|accessdate=19 October 2019|website=Correio da Manh\u00e3}}</ref> Initially, Diego Simeone thought his injury wasn't serious, until a Atletico Madrid's medical team revealed that the ankle injury could be a serious injury, leading him to be sidelined for one month.<ref>{{cite_web|url=https://www.cmjornal.pt/desporto/futebol/detalhe/saiba-qual-o-tempo-de-paragem-de-joao-felix-apos-lesao|title=Saiba qual o tempo de paragem de Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix ap\u00f3s les\u00e3o|accessdate=20 October 2019|website=Correio da Manh\u00e3}}</ref> He made his return on 23 November in a 1-1 away draw against [[Granada CF]].<ref>{{cite_web|url=https://www.laliga.com/en-GB/match/temporada-2019-2020-laliga-santander-granada-cf-atletico-de-madrid-14|title=Atl\u00e9tico de Madrid vs. Granada|accessdate=23 November 2019|website=La Liga}}</ref> During this time, F\u00e9lix was nominated as one amongst 30 candidates for [[2019 Ballon d'Or|2019]] [[Ballon d'Or]].<ref>{{cite_web|url=https://www.theportugalnews.com/news/ronaldo-felix-and-silva-nominated-for-ballon-dor/51730|title=Ronaldo, F\u00e9lix and Silva nominated for Ballon d\u00b4Or|accessdate=25 October 2019|website=The Portugal News}}</ref> On 27 November, he became the second Portuguese player, after [[Renato Sanches]], to win the [[Golden Boy Award|Golden Boy award]] for best European player under the age of 21, ahead of [[Borussia Dortmund]]'s [[Jadon Sancho]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/50570064|title=Golden Boy award: Joao Felix named best under-21 player in Europe|date=27 November 2019|website=BBC Sport}}</ref> In December, F\u00e9lix ended 28th place in the voting polls for the [[2019 Ballon d'Or]].<ref>{{cite_web|url=https://www.manisteenews.com/sports/article/US-soccer-star-Rapinoe-wins-Ballon-d-Or-14876298.php|title=Megan Rapinoe, Lionel Messi win Ballon d\u2019Or awards|accessdate=2 December 2019|website=News Manistee Advocate|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191203150930/https://www.manisteenews.com/sports/article/US-soccer-star-Rapinoe-wins-Ballon-d-Or-14876298.php|archive-date=3 December 2019|url-status=dead}}</ref> Over the following months, F\u00e9lix started to have difficulties on adapting to Diego Simeone's playing style, with Simeone trying to find his ideal position either as a [[Midfielder#Winger|right winger]] or [[second striker]], and also the fact that forwards press a lot, ended up wearing him out, while also being unable to create scoring chances with the ball off his feet,<ref>{{cite_web|url=https://www.noticiasaominuto.com/desporto/1408480/joao-felix-nao-esta-feliz-no-atletico-o-sistema-de-simeone-desgasta-o|title=\"Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix n\u00e3o est\u00e1 feliz no Atl\u00e9tico. O sistema de Simeone desgasta-o\"|accessdate=2 February 2020|website=Sapo Desporto}}</ref> leading Spanish newspaper ''[[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]]'' to name him one of the disappointing transfers of the season.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sol.sapo.pt/artigo/682102/joao-felix-entre-as-desilusoes-da-la-liga|title=Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix entre as desilus\u00f5es da La Liga|website=Jornal SOL|date=6 January 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 9 January 2020, F\u00e9lix made his debut in the [[2019\u201320 Supercopa de Espa\u00f1a|Supercopa de Espa\u00f1a]], providing an assist for [[Koke (footballer, born 1992)|Koke]] in a 3-2 victory against [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]] in the semifinal.<ref>{{cite_web|url=https://www.laliga.com/en-GB/match/temporada-2019-2020-supercopa-de-espana-fc-barcelona-atletico-de-madrid-1|title=Supercopa de Espa\u00f1a semifinal|accessdate=9 January 2020|website=La Liga}}</ref> During the match, F\u00e9lix was involved in a altercation with [[Jordi Alba]] and his teammates [[Lionel Messi]] and [[Luis Suarez]].<ref>{{cite_web|url=https://www.dn.pt/desportos/joao-felix-e-messi-pegados-no-intervalo-do-barcelona-at-madrid-11689592.html|title=Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix e Messi pegados no intervalo do Barcelona-At. Madrid|accessdate=9 January 2020|website=Di\u00e1rio de Not\u00edcias}}</ref> On 12 January, Atletico Madrid lost to their [[Madrid Derby|rivals]] [[Real Madrid]] 4\u20131 on penalties in the final.<ref>{{cite_web|url=https://www.laliga.com/en-GB/match/temporada-2019-2020-supercopa-de-espana-real-madrid-atletico-de-madrid-2|title=Supercopa de Espa\u00f1a final|accessdate=12 January 2020|website=La Liga}}</ref> On 23 January, F\u00e9lix made his [[2019\u201320 Copa del Rey|Copa del Rey]] debut in the Round of 32, provind an assist for [[\u00c1ngel Correa]] in a 2-1 loss against [[Cultural y Deportiva Leonesa|Cultural Leonesa]].<ref>{{cite_web|url=https://www.laliga.com/en-GB/match/temporada-2019-2020-copa-del-rey-cultural-leonesa-atletico-de-madrid-3|title=Copa del Rey round of 32|accessdate=23 January 2020|website=La Liga}}</ref> Three days later, F\u00e9lix suffered a second injury on his leg in a 0-0 home draw against CD Legan\u00e9s, sidelining him again for a month, leading him to miss to Atletico Madrid's next three league matches, which included the second [[Madrid Derby]] of the season and Atletico Madrid's first leg of their round of 16 Champions League against [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.abola.pt/nnh/2020-01-29/atletico-madrid-joao-felix-lesiona-se-e-esta-em-duvida-para-o-derbi/826785|title=JO\u00c3O F\u00c9LIX LESIONA-SE E EST\u00c1 EM D\u00daVIDA PARA O D\u00c9RBI|website=A Bola|date=26 January 2020}}</ref> He made his return on 23 February, replacing Vitolo in the 57th minute, scoring the third goal in a 3-1 home victory against [[Villarreal CF|Villarreal]].<ref>{{cite_web|url=https://www.laliga.com/en-GB/match/temporada-2019-2020-laliga-santander-atletico-de-madrid-villarreal-cf-25|accessdate=23 February 2020|title=Atletico Madrid vs Villarreal|website=La Liga}}</ref> On 11 March 2020, during [[Overtime (sports)|extra time]] of the [[2019\u201320 UEFA Champions League|Champions League round-of-16 tie]] away to [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]] in the second leg, F\u00e9lix provided an assist for [[Marcos Llorente]] in an eventual 3\u20132 win and qualification to the quarterfinals of the Champions League.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/sport/football/liverpool-vs-atletico-madrid-live-score-champions-league-result-a4385036.html?amp|title=Liverpool crash out of Champions League to Atletico Madrid \u2013 LIVE! Latest news and result reaction|newspaper=[[Evening Standard]]|last=Doyle|first=Tom|date=11 March 2020|accessdate=11 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\n===Youth===\nOn 14 June 2017, F\u00e9lix began his international career with [[Portugal national under-18 football team|Portugal's under-18 team]], debuting against [[Norway national under-18 football team|Norway]], replacing [[Elves Bald\u00e9]] in the 58th minute. In this friendly match, F\u00e9lix scored two goals in a 3\u20130 victory in Lisbon. On 10 October 2017, F\u00e9lix debuted for [[Portugal national under-21 football team|Portugal's under-21 team]] for the qualification of the [[2019 UEFA European Under-21 Championship]], in a 3\u20131 defeat against [[Bosnia and Herzegovina national under-21 football team|Bosnia and Herzegovina]], replacing [[Xadas]] in the 56th minute.<ref>{{cite web|title=UEFA Bosnia and Herzegovina vs Portugal qualification for the 2019 UEFA European Under-21 Championship debut|url=https://pt.uefa.com/under21/season=2019/matches/round=2000803/match=2022501/|access-date=3 September 2019|website=[[UEFA]]|date=10 October 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=B\u00f3snia-Portugal, 3\u20131: Primeira derrota em apuramentos em 6 anos|url=https://www.record.pt/internacional/competicoes-de-selecoes/europeu-sub-21/detalhe/sub-21-bosnia-portugal-em-direto|access-date=3 September 2019|newspaper=Record|date=10 October 2017}}</ref>\n\nOn 15 January 2018, F\u00e9lix debuted for [[Portugal national under-19 football team|Portugal's under-19 team]] as a 27th minute substitute for an injured Jorge Teixeira in a 2\u20131 win over [[Turkey national under-19 football team|Turkey]]. On 23 March 2018, F\u00e9lix scored his first international goal for Portugal's under-21 team in a 7\u20130 thrashing of [[Liechtenstein national under-21 football team|Liechtenstein]].<ref>{{cite news|title=UEFA Liechtenstein vs Portugal qualification for the 2019 UEFA European Under-21 Championship debut|url=https://pt.uefa.com/under21/season=2019/matches/round=2000803/match=2022482/|access-date=3 September 2019|publisher=UEFA|date=23 March 2018}}</ref> In the end of the qualification process, he had scored four goals, helping guide Portugal to the [[2019 UEFA European Under-21 Championship qualification play-offs|play-offs]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Brilho de uma gera\u00e7\u00e3o deu para o playoff, para j\u00e1|url=https://www.zerozero.pt/news.php?id=233064|access-date=3 September 2019|work=zerozero|date=23 March 2018}}</ref> In the first leg of the play-offs, Portugal faced [[Poland national under-21 football team|Poland]] in a 1\u20130 away victory, but eventually lost in the second leg in a 3\u20131 home defeat, failing to qualify for the tournament.<ref>{{cite news|title=Play-offs 1st leg|url=https://pt.uefa.com/under21/season=2019/matches/round=2000804/match=2025681/|access-date=3 September 2019|publisher=UEFA|date=16 November 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Play-offs 2nd leg|url=https://pt.uefa.com/under21/season=2019/matches/round=2000804/match=2025682/|access-date=3 September 2019|publisher=UEFA|date=20 November 2018}}</ref>\n\nDuring his international youth career, F\u00e9lix would go on to represent the under-18, under-19 and under-21 teams, amassing 14 youth caps and scoring 6 goals overall.{{citation needed|date=March 2020}}\n\n===Senior===\nOn 15 March 2019, manager [[Fernando Santos (Portuguese footballer)|Fernando Santos]] called up F\u00e9lix to the [[Portugal national football team|senior team]] for the first time, ahead of the opening [[UEFA Euro 2020 qualifying]] matches.<ref>{{cite news|date=15 March 2019|title=Eagles called up to the national team|url=https://www.slbenfica.pt/en-us/agora/noticias/2018-2019/03/15/futebol-jogadores-benfica-convocados-selecao-portugal-jogos-ucrania-e-servia-apuramento-europeu|publisher=S.L. Benfica|access-date=5 July 2019}}</ref> During training with the national squad, F\u00e9lix injured his foot and thus missed Portugal's match against [[Serbia national football team|Serbia]] on 25 March.<ref>{{cite news|last=Barbosa|first=Nuno|date=25 March 2019|title=UEFA deixa lesionado Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix de fora do Portugal\u2013S\u00e9rvia|trans-title=UEFA leaves injured Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix out of Portugal\u2013Serbia|url=https://www.jn.pt/desporto/interior/uefa-deixa-lesionado-joao-felix-de-fora-do-portugal-servia-10721509.html|language=pt|newspaper=[[Jornal de Not\u00edcias]]|access-date=5 July 2019}}</ref>\n\nF\u00e9lix was also selected for the [[2019 UEFA Nations League Finals]] squad on home soil.<ref>{{cite news|title=Portugal name Cristiano Ronaldo and Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix in Nations League squad|url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/13954/11727023/portugal-name-cristiano-ronaldo-and-joao-felix-in-nations-league-squad|access-date=27 May 2019|work=[[Sky Sports]]|date=24 May 2019}}</ref> He made his international debut for the senior team on 5 June against [[Switzerland national football team|Switzerland]] in the semi-finals, where he was substituted in the 71st minute of a 3\u20131 win.<ref>{{cite news|title=Joao Felix is rated at \u00a3106m but he struggled on his Portugal debut|url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/13954/11735790/joao-felix-is-rated-at-106m-but-he-struggled-on-his-portugal-debut|access-date=6 June 2019|work=Sky Sports|date=6 June 2019}}</ref> Four days later, Portugal defeated [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands]] 1\u20130 in the tournament's final.<ref>{{cite news|last=Law|first=Matt|title=Result: Goncalo Guedes scores winner as Portugal land UEFA Nations League title|url=https://www.sportsmole.co.uk/football/portugal/uefa-nations-league/result/result-guedes-scores-winner-as-portugal-land-nations-league-title_361579.html|access-date=9 June 2019|work=Sports Mole|date=5 July 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Style of play==\nConsidered by Benfica to be one of the most promising players to have emerged from their [[S.L. Benfica Juniors|youth ranks]], as well as regarded considered by pundits as one of the most talented young players in world football,<ref name=\"en.as.com\"/><ref name=\"paraeles\"/> F\u00e9lix is a highly skilful and technical player,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.cnn.com/2019/04/17/sport/joao-felix-benfica-spt-intl/index.html |title=Joao Felix: The Benfica teen who is a 'star already' |publisher=CNN |last1=Macguire |first1=Eoghan |date=7 May 2019 |accessdate=11 April 2020 }}</ref> who is capable of playing in several offensive positions, due to his versatility; throughout his career, he has been deployed as a [[Striker (association football)|striker]], as a [[Forward (association football)#Second striker|second striker]], or even as a [[Midfielder#Winger|winger]], although his primary position is that of an [[attacking midfielder]].<ref name=\"en.as.com\"/><ref>{{cite news|url=https://observador.pt/2018/08/25/joao-felix-o-miudo-dos-pestinhas-que-saiu-do-fc-porto-por-ser-magricelas-e-esta-a-ganhar-cabedal-no-benfica/|title=Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix, o mi\u00fado dos Pestinhas que saiu do FC Porto por ser magricelas e est\u00e1 a ganhar cabedal no Benfica|trans-title=Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix, the Pestinhas kid who left FC Porto for being scrawny and is gaining muscle at Benfica|newspaper=Observador|language=pt|last=Roseiro|first=Bruno|date=25 August 2018||access-date=17 January 2019}}</ref> With Benfica, F\u00e9lix usually played as a second striker in a [[Formation (association football)#4\u20134\u20132|4\u20134\u20132 formation]], where he was tasked with linking up the midfield with the attack, as well as creating opportunities for the team's main striker, while also being given the freedom to make runs into the box and score goals himself.<ref name=\"en.as.com\"/><ref name=\"davis\"/> With Atl\u00e9tico Madrid, he has occasionally played in a similar role, but has often been deployed as a right winger in the team's 4\u20134\u20132 formation.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.marca.com/en/football/spanish-football/2020/02/25/5e5510c222601d46538b459b.html |title=Joao Felix is finally seeing the light |publisher=Marca |last1=Medina |first1=David G. |date=25 February 2020 |accessdate=11 April 2020 }}</ref> A quick and intelligent player, with an eye for goal, his primary traits are his speed, creativity, finishing, touch on the ball, and [[Dribbling#Association football|dribbling]] skills, as well as his vision and precise passing.<ref name=\"en.as.com\"/><ref name=DiarioNoticias></ref>{{cite web |url=https://bleacherreport.com/articles/2858128-matthijs-de-ligt-joao-felix-jadon-sancho-on-20-man-2019-golden-boy-shortlist |title=Matthijs de Ligt, Joao Felix, Jadon Sancho on 20-Man 2019 Golden Boy Shortlist |publisher=Bleacher Report |last1=Jones |first1=Matt |date=15 October 2019 |accessdate=8 March 2020 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://ca.sports.yahoo.com/news/atletico-madrids-joao-felix-is-the-best-signing-of-the-summer-183220159.html |title=Atletico Madrid's Joao Felix is the best signing of the summer |publisher=Yahoo Sports |last1=Bailey |first1=Ryan |date=29 July 2019 |accessdate=8 March 2020 }}</ref> His playing style has led him to be compared to Brazilian former [[playmaker]] [[Kak\u00e1]] and former Benfica players [[Rui Costa]] and [[Jo\u00e3o Pinto]].<ref name=\"en.as.com\"/><ref name=\"paraeles\"/>\n\n==Personal life==\nF\u00e9lix's parents, Carlos (father) and Carla (mother), are both teachers. He has a younger brother, Hugo, who plays for Benfica youth ranks.<ref name=lb/> Growing up, F\u00e9lix's idols were Kak\u00e1 and Rui Costa, the latter a player he looked to emulate.<ref>{{cite news|title=Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix fala de tudo. As praxes, os \u00eddolos, a rela\u00e7\u00e3o com Vieira, o n.\u00ba 10 e a Bola de Ouro|trans-title=Jo\u00e3o Felix talks about everything. The pranks, the idols, the relationship with Vieira, the number 10 and the Golden Ball|url=https://www.dn.pt/desportos/interior/joao-felix-fala-de-tudo-as-praxes-os-idolos-a-relacao-com-vieira-o-n10-e-a-bola-de-ouro-10938513.html|newspaper=Di\u00e1rio de Not\u00edcias|date=24 May 2019|language=pt}}</ref> F\u00e9lix is in a relationship with Portuguese actress Margarida Corceiro, with the couple being discrete about their relationship at first, but later Corceiro publicly revealed it.<ref>{{cite news|title=Margarida Corceiro conta como come\u00e7ou a namorar com Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix|url=https://selfie.iol.pt/voce-na-tv/manuel-luis-goucha/margarida-corceiro-conta-como-comecou-a-namorar-com-joao-felix|date=7 February 2020|language=pt}}</ref>\n\nOn April 14, 2020, F\u00e9lix made a donation of equipment to a crowdfunding campaign to an hospital in his hometown in [[Viseu]] to help with the struggle of the [[COVID-19 pandemic|Coronavirus (COVID-19) pandemic]].<ref>vidas.pt/a-ferver/detalhe/joao-felix-mostra-se-solidario-e-faz-donativo-a-hospital</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n===Club===\n{{updated|match played 11 March 2020}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|+ Appearances and goals by club, season and competition\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!colspan=\"3\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|National Cup{{efn|Includes [[Ta\u00e7a de Portugal]], [[Copa del Rey]]}}\n!colspan=\"2\"|League Cup{{efn|Includes [[Ta\u00e7a da Liga]]}}\n!colspan=\"2\"|Europe\n!colspan=\"2\"|Other\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n!Division!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\"|[[S.L. Benfica B|Benfica B]]\n|[[2016\u201317 LigaPro|2016\u201317]]<ref name=\"Soccerway\"/>\n|[[LigaPro]]\n|13||3||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||13||3\n|-\n|[[2017\u201318 LigaPro|2017\u201318]]<ref name=\"Soccerway\"/>\n|LigaPro\n|17||4||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||17||4\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n!30||7||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||30||7\n|-\n|[[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]]\n|[[2018\u201319 S.L. Benfica season|2018\u201319]]<ref name=\"Soccerway\"/><ref>For Ta\u00e7a de Portugal third round: {{cite news|url=https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/taca-de-portugal/detalhe/sertanense-benfica-em-direto|title=Sertanense-Benfica, 0\u20133|newspaper=Record|date=18 October 2018|access-date=2 March 2020|language=Portuguese}}</ref>\n|[[Primeira Liga]]\n|26||15||6||1||2||1||9{{efn|Three appearances in [[UEFA Champions League]], six appearances and three goals in [[UEFA Europa League]]}}||3||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||43||20\n|-\n|[[Atl\u00e9tico Madrid]]\n|[[2019\u201320 Atl\u00e9tico Madrid season|2019\u201320]]<ref name=\"Soccerway\">{{cite web|url=https://uk.soccerway.com/players/joao-felix--sequeira/459986/|title=Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix: Summary|website=Soccerway|publisher=Perform Group|access-date=2 March 2020}}</ref>\n|[[La Liga]]\n|20||4||1||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||5{{efn|Appearances in UEFA Champions League}}||2||2{{efn|Appearances in [[Supercopa de Espa\u00f1a]]}}||0||28||6\n|-\n!colspan=\"3\"|Career total\n!76||26||7||1||2||1||14||5||2||0||101||33\n|}\n\n{{notelist}}\n\n===International===\n{{updated|match played 14 October 2019}}<ref>{{NFT player |pid=74472 |name=Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix |accessdate=2 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|+ Appearances and goals by national team and year\n|-\n!National team!!Year!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|[[Portugal national football team|Portugal]]\n|2019||5||0\n|-\n!colspan=2|Total||5||0\n|}\n\n==Honours==\n'''Benfica'''\n*[[Primeira Liga]]: [[2018\u201319 Primeira Liga|2018\u201319]]<ref name=\"Soccerway\"/>\n*[[Campeonato Nacional de Juniores]]: 2017\u201318<ref name=\"Soccerway\"/>\n*[[UEFA Youth League]] runner-up: [[2016\u201317 UEFA Youth League|2016\u201317]]<ref name=\"Soccerway\"/>\n\n'''Portugal'''\n*[[UEFA Nations League]]: [[2018\u201319 UEFA Nations League|2018\u201319]]<ref name=\"Soccerway\"/>\n\n'''Individual'''\n*[[Primeira Liga]] Player of the Month: January 2019<ref>{{cite news|date=12 February 2019|title=Melhores de janeiro: Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix e Pedro Henrique em destaque|trans-title=Best of January: Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix and Pedro Henrique in evidence|url=http://www.ligaportugal.pt/pt/epocas/20182019/noticias/geral/premios/melhores-de-janeiro-joao-felix-e-pedro-henrique-em-destaque/|language=pt|publisher=[[Liga Portugal]]|access-date=14 February 2019}}</ref>\n*[[SJPF Young Player of the Month]]: January 2019<ref>{{cite news|date=14 February 2019|title=Sindicato tamb\u00e9m distingue Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix|trans-title=Syndicate also distinguish Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix|url=https://www.abola.pt/Clubes/Noticias/Ver/773678/40|url-status=dead|language=pt|newspaper=A Bola|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190217030216/https://www.abola.pt/Clubes/Noticias/Ver/773678/40|archive-date=17 February 2019|access-date=16 February 2019}}</ref>\n*[[UEFA Europa League]] Squad of the Season: [[2018\u201319 UEFA Europa League#Squad of the Season|2018\u201319]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/news/newsid=2606568.html|title=UEFA Europa League Squad of the 2018/19 Season|website=UEFA|date=30 May 2019}}</ref>\n*[[CNID Footballer of the Year|CNID Best Revelation Footballer of the Year]]: 2019<ref>{{cite web|url=https://desporto.sapo.pt/futebol/primeira-liga/artigos/bruno-fernandes-eleito-futebolista-da-i-liga-pelos-associados-do-cnid|title=Bruno Fernandes eleito futebolista da I Liga pelos associados do CNID|trans-title=Bruno Fernandes voted footballer of I League by CNID members|website=SAPO Desporto|language=pt|date=21 May 2019|access-date=1 June 2019}}</ref>\n*Primeira Liga's Best Young Player of the Year: [[2018\u201319 Primeira Liga|2018\u201319]]<ref>{{cite news|date=5 July 2019|title=Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix eleito Jogador Jovem do Ano de 2018/2019|trans-title=Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix elected 2018\u201319 Young Player of the Year|url=https://desporto.sapo.pt/futebol/primeira-liga/artigos/joao-felix-eleito-jogador-jovem-do-ano-de-20182019|language=pt|work=SAPO Desporto|access-date=6 July 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Golden Globes (Portugal)|Golden Globes]]: 2019 [[Golden Globe (Portugal) for Best Newcomer|Best Newcomer]]<ref>{{cite news|date=30 September 2019|title=Os Globos de Ouro foram para...|trans-title=The Golden Globes went to...|url=https://sicnoticias.pt/cultura/2019-09-30-Os-Globos-de-Ouro-foram-para|language=pt|work=[[SIC Not\u00edcias]]|access-date=30 September 2019}}</ref>\n*A Bola Player of the Year: 2019<ref>{{cite video|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3zU5d0ZsY2I|title=Entrevista a Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix- Jogador do ano para o jornal A BOLA.|author=A Bola TV|publisher=[[YouTube]]|accessdate=January 7, 2020}}</ref> \n*[[Golden Boy (award)|Golden Boy]]: 2019<ref name=\"GoldenBoy\"/>\n* [[Globe Soccer Awards|Globe Revelation Player]]: 2019<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.jn.pt/desporto/cristiano-ronaldo-e-joao-felix-ganham-globe-soccer-awards-11659548.html|title=Cristiano Ronaldo e Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix ganham Globe Soccer Awards|newspaper=Jornal de Not\u00edcias |date=29 December 2019 |accessdate=29 December 2019}}</ref>\n* [[Ballon d'Or]]: [[2019 Ballon d'Or|2019]] (28th place)<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.francefootball.fr/diaporama/Le-classement-complet-du-ballon-d-or-france-football-2019/7777/#30|title=The complete ranking of the Ballon d'Or France Football 2019 |newspaper=France Football |date=2 December 2019 |accessdate=9 December 2019}}</ref>\n* [[Kopa Trophy]]: 3rd place ([[2019 Ballon d'Or|2019]])<ref>{{cite news |title=De Ligt wint Kopa Trophy voor 's werelds beste speler tot 21 jaar |url=https://www.nu.nl/voetbal/6015102/de-ligt-wint-kopa-trophy-voor-s-werelds-beste-speler-tot-21-jaar.html |website=[[NU.nl]] |date=2 December 2019 |accessdate=2 December 2019 |language=Dutch}}</ref>\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist|group=n}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category}}\n*[https://en.atleticodemadrid.com/jugadores/jo-o-felix-2019-2020 Atl\u00e9tico Madrid official profile]\n*[https://www.fpf.pt/pt/Jogadores/Jogador/playerId/849913 National team data] {{in lang|pt}}\n*{{UEFA player}}\n*{{ForaDeJogo}}\n\n{{Atl\u00e9tico Madrid squad}}\n{{Golden Boy award winners}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Felix, Joao}}\n[[Category:1999 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Viseu]]\n[[Category:Portuguese footballers]]\n[[Category:Portugal youth international footballers]]\n[[Category:Portugal under-21 international footballers]]\n[[Category:Portugal international footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n[[Category:FC Porto players]]\n[[Category:Padroense F.C. players]]\n[[Category:S.L. Benfica B players]]\n[[Category:S.L. Benfica footballers]]\n[[Category:Atl\u00e9tico Madrid footballers]]\n[[Category:LigaPro players]]\n[[Category:Primeira Liga players]]\n[[Category:La Liga players]]\n[[Category:Golden Globes (Portugal) winners]]\n[[Category:Portuguese expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Spain]]\n[[Category:Portuguese expatriate sportspeople in Spain]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Portuguese association football player}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2016}}\n{{Portuguese name|F\u00e9lix|Sequeira}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n|name = Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix\n|image = Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix 2019.jpg\n|image_size = \n|caption = F\u00e9lix with [[Atl\u00e9tico Madrid]] in 2019\n|fullname = Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix Sequeira<ref>{{cite web|url=http://actas.rfef.es/actas/RFEF_CmpActa1?cod_primaria=1000144&CodActa=60726|title=Acta del Partido celebrado el 01 de marzo de 2020, en Barcelona|trans-title=Minutes of the Match held on 1 March 2020, in Barcelona|publisher=Royal Spanish Football Federation|access-date=2 March 2020|language=Spanish}}</ref>\n|birth_date = {{birth date and age|1999|11|10|df=y}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/player/_/id/276350/joao-felix|title=Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix|publisher=ESPN|access-date=2 March 2020}}</ref>\n|birth_place = [[Viseu]], Portugal\n|height = 1.81 m<ref>{{cite web|url=https://en.atleticodemadrid.com/jugadores/jo-o-felix-2019-2020-2|title=Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix|publisher=Atl\u00e9tico Madrid|access-date=2 March 2020}}</ref>\n|position = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]]\n|currentclub = [[Atl\u00e9tico Madrid]]\n|clubnumber = 7\n|youthyears1 = 2007\u20132008\n|youthclubs1 = Os Pestinhas\n|youthyears2 = 2008\u20132015\n|youthclubs2 = [[FC Porto|Porto]]\n|youthyears3 = 2014\u20132015\n|youthclubs3 = \u2192 [[Padroense F.C.|Padroense]] (loan)\n|youthyears4 = 2015\u20132018\n|youthclubs4 = [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]]\n|years1 = 2016\u20132018\n|clubs1 = [[S.L. Benfica B|Benfica B]]\n|caps1 = 30\n|goals1 = 7\n|years2 = 2018\u20132019\n|clubs2 = [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]]\n|caps2 = 26\n|goals2 = 15\n|years3 = 2019\u2013\n|clubs3 = [[Atl\u00e9tico Madrid]]\n|caps3 = 20\n|goals3 = 4\n|nationalyears1 = 2017\n|nationalteam1 = [[Portugal national under-18 football team|Portugal U18]]\n|nationalcaps1 = 2\n|nationalgoals1 = 2\n|nationalyears2 = 2018\n|nationalteam2 = [[Portugal national under-19 football team|Portugal U19]]\n|nationalcaps2 = 2\n|nationalgoals2 = 0\n|nationalyears3 = 2017\u2013\n|nationalteam3 = [[Portugal national under-21 football team|Portugal U21]]\n|nationalcaps3 = 10\n|nationalgoals3 = 4\n|nationalyears4 = 2019\u2013\n|nationalteam4 = [[Portugal national football team|Portugal]]\n|nationalcaps4 = 5\n|nationalgoals4 = 0\n|club-update = 17:16, 7 March 2020 (UTC)\n|nationalteam-update = 00:24, 2 March 2020 (UTC)\n|medaltemplates = {{MedalSport|Men's [[Association football|football]]}}\n{{medalCountry|[[Portugal national football team|Portugal]]}}\n{{medalCompetition|[[UEFA Nations League]]}}\n{{medal|Winner|[[2019 UEFA Nations League Finals|2019 Portugal]]|}}\n}}\n'''Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix Sequeira''' ({{IPA-pt|\u0292u\u02c8\u0250\u0303w \u02c8f\u025bliks|}};{{refn|group=n|Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix himself pronounces his name as {{IPA-pt|-liks|}},<ref name=pron>{{cite media|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=OhOKReTdYLM&t=60|title=Entrevista Campe\u00e3o37 \u2013 Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix|date=2019-05-24|last=|first=|type=|language=|publisher=[[S.L. Benfica]]|time=60 seconds|via=[[YouTube]]}}</ref> but this name is also commonly pronounced {{IPA-pt|-li\u0283|}}.<ref name=pron/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://ciberduvidas.iscte-iul.pt/aberturas/tipos-de-texto-o-nome-felix-os-lusismos-do-ingles-o-escritor-nelson-rodrigues-e-a-diversidade-lingui/2413|title=Tipos de texto, o (sempre mal dito) nome F\u00e9lix, 10 lusismos do ingl\u00eas, e algumas das express\u00f5es mais saborosas de Nelson Rodrigues|date=4 February 2019|website=Ciberd\u00favidas da L\u00edngua Portuguesa|language=pt|trans-title=Types of text, the (always badly spelt) ''F\u00e9lix'' name, 10 English ''lusismos'', and some of the tastiest expressions of Nelson Rodrigues|access-date=5 March 2019}}</ref>}} born 10 November 1999) is a Portuguese professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]] for Spanish [[La Liga]] club [[Atl\u00e9tico Madrid]] and the [[Portugal national football team|Portugal national team]]. He is known for his speed, finishing, technique and his [[Dribbling#Association football|dribbling]] and he can also play as a [[Midfielder#Winger|winger]] or an [[Midfielder#Attacking midfielder|attacking midfielder]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://bleacherreport.com/articles/2858128-matthijs-de-ligt-joao-felix-jadon-sancho-on-20-man-2019-golden-boy-shortlist |title=Matthijs de Ligt, Joao Felix, Jadon Sancho on 20-Man 2019 Golden Boy Shortlist |publisher=Bleacher Report |last1=Jones |first1=Matt |date=15 October 2019 |accessdate=8 March 2020 }}</ref><ref name=\"en.as.com\">{{cite web |url=https://en.as.com/en/2019/06/18/football/1560852116_870651.html |title=Tactical analysis of Joao F\u00e9lix: a difference-making transfer |publisher=AS |last1=Sill\u00e9s |first1=Javier |date=18 June 2019 |accessdate=8 March 2020 }}</ref>\n\nF\u00e9lix initially trained at [[FC Porto|Porto]]'s youth ranks before moving to rivals [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]] in 2015. He began playing for the latter's [[S.L. Benfica B|reserve team]] a year later and was promoted to the first-team in 2018, making his professional debut at age 18. He then starred as a goalscorer and helped Benfica win the [[2018\u201319 Primeira Liga|league title]] in [[2018\u201319 S.L. Benfica season|his first and only season with them]], and was awarded Primeira Liga's Best Young Player of the Year and the [[Golden Boy (award)|Golden Boy]] award.<ref name=\"GoldenBoy\">{{cite web |url=https://www.tuttosport.com/news/calcio/golden-boy/2019/11/27-63853409/il_profilo_del_golden_boy_joo_flix_il_predestinato/|title=Il profilo del Golden Boy Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix: il predestinato|trans-title=The profile of the Golden Boy Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix: the predestined|date=27 November 2019 |publisher=Tuttosport|language=it|accessdate=27 November 2019}}</ref> Internationally, he became the youngest ever player to score a [[hat-trick]] in the [[UEFA Europa League]], aged 19.\n\nF\u00e9lix's performances sparked the interest of several European clubs, with Atl\u00e9tico Madrid signing him in 2019 for a club-record transfer worth \u20ac126&nbsp;million (\u00a3113&nbsp;million), the [[List of most expensive association football transfers|fourth-most expensive football transfer]], the second-most ever paid for a teenager and the highest fee for a Portuguese player leaving the domestic league. Shortly after, F\u00e9lix was listed among the shortlist for the [[Ballon d'Or]] and finished third for the [[Kopa Trophy]] in 2019.<ref name=\"BallonDOr\">{{cite news |url=https://www.francefootball.fr/diaporama/Le-classement-complet-du-ballon-d-or-france-football-2019/7777/#30|title=The complete ranking of the Ballon d'Or France Football 2019 |newspaper=France Football |date=2 December 2019 |accessdate=9 December 2019}}</ref>\n\nAfter being [[Cap (sport)|capped]] for Portugal's youth teams at [[Portugal national under-18 football team|under-18]], [[Portugal national under-19 football team|under-19]] and [[Portugal national under-21 football team|under-21]] levels, F\u00e9lix made his senior debut in the semi-finals of the [[2019 UEFA Nations League Finals]], won by Portugal on home soil.\n\n==Club career==\n===Early career===\nBorn in [[Viseu]],<ref name=\"Soccerway\"/> F\u00e9lix started playing football at Os Pestinhas in 2007 before joining the youth ranks of [[FC Porto]] a year later, aged eight.<ref name=DiarioNoticias>{{cite news |url=https://www.dn.pt/desportos/benfica-segura-joao-felix-o-miudo-franzino-que-nao-foi-aproveitado-pelo-fc-porto-10114601.html |title=Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix, o mi\u00fado franzino que o FC Porto n\u00e3o aproveitou |trans-title=Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix, the skinny kid that Porto did not take advantage of |work=Di\u00e1rio de Not\u00edcias |language=Portuguese |last1=Fernandes |first1=Nuno |date=5 November 2018 |accessdate=8 March 2020 }}</ref> After F\u00e9lix moved to [[Porto]], he faced some challenges such as extensive schedules that included daily shuttle hours between Viseu and Porto.<ref name=lb>{{cite web|title=Hist\u00f3ria da inf\u00e2ncia do Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix e fatos incont\u00e1veis de biografia|trans-title=Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix's childhood story and countless facts of biography|url=https://lifebogger.com/pt/joao-felix-hist%C3%B3ria-de-inf%C3%A2ncia-mais-fatos-de-biografia-n%C3%A3o-revelada/|access-date=4 May 2019|website=Life Blogger|date=4 May 2019|language=pt}}</ref>{{Better source|reason=It does not seem to be a reliable source.|date=September 2019}} He moved to his parents' house to be near Porto's training grounds and, later, he wanted to quit football due to missing his parents, but his father convinced him on pursuing his career.<ref name=lb/> F\u00e9lix was released by Porto in 2014 because of his slight frame and moved on to [[Lisbon]] rivals [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]] in 2015, aged 15, after a season-long loan at [[Padroense F.C.|Padroense]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Azevedo|first=Pedro Miguel|title=Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix, o magricela que escapou ao FC Porto e brilha no Benfica|trans-title=Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix, the scrawny kid who slipped from FC Porto and shines for Benfica|url=https://www.ojogo.pt/futebol/1a-liga/benfica/noticias/interior/joao-felix-o-magricela-que-escapou-ao-fc-porto-e-brilha-no-benfica-6245594.html|access-date=1 February 2018|newspaper=[[O Jogo]]|date=26 April 2017|language=pt}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Paulo Ribeiro|first=Jo\u00e3o|date=19 June 2019|title=Presidente do Padroense orgulhoso pelo contributo do clube no crescimento de F\u00e9lix|trans-title=Padroense president proud of the club's contribution to the growth of Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix|url=https://rr.sapo.pt/2019/06/19/benfica/presidente-do-padroense-orgulhoso-pelo-contributo-do-clube-no-crescimento-de-felix/noticia/155267/|language=pt|work=[[R\u00e1dio Renascen\u00e7a]]|access-date=11 September 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Smith|first=Roy|author-link=Rory Smith (journalist)|date=12 September 2019|title=Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix Is in a Hurry. So Is Everyone Else.|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/09/12/sports/joao-felix-atletico-madrid.html|newspaper=[[The New York Times]]|access-date=12 September 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Benfica===\n{{quote box\n| quote = \"They've already called him my heir or the new Kaka. To be honest, Felix is just Felix. He has an extraordinary understanding of the game and the rare ability to know where to be in front of goal.\"\n| source = \u2014 [[Rui Costa]] on F\u00e9lix's playing style<ref name=\"davis\">{{cite news|last=Davis|first=Matt|title=Joao Felix: The Benfica wonderkid who has been called the most exciting player since Cristiano Ronaldo|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/48385500|access-date=27 May 2019|work=BBC Sport|date=26 May 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|date=22 March 2019|url=https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-nos/benfica/detalhe/rui-costa-sobre-joao-felix-ha-jogadores-que-nao-conseguimos-reter-em-portugal|title=Rui Costa sobre Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix: \"H\u00e1 jogadores que n\u00e3o conseguimos reter em Portugal\"|newspaper=[[Record (newspaper)|Record]]}}</ref>\n| align = right\n| width = 28%\n}}\nF\u00e9lix debuted professionally at the age of 16 for Benfica's [[S.L. Benfica B|reserve team]] in [[LigaPro]] on 17 September 2016, coming on as an 83rd-minute substitute for [[Aur\u00e9lio Buta]] in a goalless draw at [[S.C. Freamunde|Freamunde]]. In doing so, he became the youngest player to debut for Benfica B.<ref>{{cite news|last=Ponte|first=Pedro|date=17 September 2016|title=Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix \u00e9 o mais novo de sempre a jogar pelo Benfica B|trans-title=Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix is the youngest ever to play for Benfica B|url=http://www.record.xl.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-nos/benfica/detalhe/joao-felix-e-o-mais-novo-de-sempre-a-jogar-pela-benfica-b.html|language=pt|newspaper=Record|access-date=18 June 2019}}</ref> He played 13 matches and scored three goals over [[2016\u201317 LigaPro|the season]], the first being a consolation in a 2\u20131 loss to his hometown team [[Acad\u00e9mico de Viseu F.C.|Acad\u00e9mico de Viseu]] on 15 February 2017.<ref>{{cite news|title=Benfica B perde com o Acad\u00e9mico em Viseu|trans-title=Benfica B lose to Acad\u00e9mico in Viseu|url=http://www.maisfutebol.iol.pt/academico-viseu/15-02-2017/ii-liga-benfica-b-procura-3-vitoria-seguida-em-casa-do-ac-viseu|access-date=1 February 2018|work=Maisfutebol|date=15 February 2017|language=pt}}</ref> Later, on 30 January 2018, he scored a [[hat-trick]] in a 5\u20130 home win over [[F.C. Famalic\u00e3o|Famalic\u00e3o]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix marca tr\u00eas golos na goleada do Benfica B ao Famalic\u00e3o|trans-title=Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix scores three goals in Benfica B's thrashing of Famalic\u00e3o|url=https://www.dn.pt/desporto/benfica/interior/joao-felix-marca-tres-golos-na-goleada-do-benfica-b-ao-famalicao-9085800.html|access-date=1 February 2018|newspaper=[[Di\u00e1rio de Not\u00edcias]]|date=30 January 2018|language=pt}}</ref> During that season, F\u00e9lix played in the [[2016\u201317 UEFA Youth League]], in which he was a key part of Benfica reaching the final of the competition, lost to [[FC Red Bull Salzburg|Red Bull Salzburg]] (2\u20131); he scored six goals in the tournament.{{citation needed|date=March 2020}}\n\nF\u00e9lix was then promoted to Benfica's first team for the [[2018\u201319 S.L. Benfica season|2018\u201319 season]], making his debut in a 2\u20130 [[Primeira Liga]] win at [[Boavista F.C.|Boavista]] on 18 August. A week later, he scored his first Primeira Liga goal, thus becoming the youngest player to score in the [[Derby de Lisboa|Lisbon derby]], which ended in a 1\u20131 tie.<ref>{{cite news|title=Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix: \"I shivered\"|url=https://www.slbenfica.pt/en-us/agora/noticias/2018-2019/08/25/joao-felix-declaracoes-futebol-benfica-sporting-derbi-3-jornada-liga-nos|access-date=25 August 2018|publisher=[[S.L. Benfica]]|date=25 August 2018}}</ref> On 16 January 2019, he scored the qualifying goal against [[Vit\u00f3ria S.C.|Vit\u00f3ria de Guimar\u00e3es]] in the [[Ta\u00e7a de Portugal|Portuguese Cup]] quarter-finals.<ref>{{cite news|date=15 January 2019|title=Golo de Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix apura Benfica para as meias-finais da Ta\u00e7a de Portugal|trans-title=F\u00e9lix's goal qualifies Benfica to the Portuguese Cup semi-finals|url=https://24.sapo.pt/desporto/artigos/golo-de-joao-felix-apura-benfica-para-as-meias-finais-da-taca-de-portugal|language=pt|work=[[SAPO (company)|SAPO]] Desporto|access-date=8 February 2019}}</ref> After [[Bruno Lage]] took over as coach of Benfica, his first decision was to use F\u00e9lix more regularly, partnering him with [[Haris Seferovi\u0107]] in the attack.<ref>{{cite news|last=Oliveira|first=Diogo Cardoso|date=23 May 2019|title=A primeira decis\u00e3o de Lage: \"Meter o mi\u00fado Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix a jogar\"|trans-title=Lage's first decision: \"To put the kid Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix playing\"|url=https://www.publico.pt/2019/05/23/desporto/noticia/lage-recorda-primeira-decisao-treinador-meter-miudo-joao-felix-jogar-1873832|language=pt|newspaper=[[P\u00fablico (Portugal)|P\u00fablico]]|access-date=5 July 2019}}</ref> Later on, F\u00e9lix was praised for his performance in a 4\u20132 away win over [[Sporting CP]] in the league on 3 February,<ref name=\"paraeles\">{{cite news|last=Martins|first=Andr\u00e9 Cruz|date=6 February 2019|title=Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix, uma mistura de Rui Costa e Jo\u00e3o Pinto com tra\u00e7os de Cruyff|trans-title=Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix, a mixture of Rui Costa and Jo\u00e3o Pinto with Cruyff traits|url=https://www.paraeles.pt/desporto/joao-felix-uma-mistura-de-rui-costa-e-joao-pinto-com-tracos-de-cruyff/|language=pt|work=Para Eles|access-date=14 February 2019}}</ref> subsequently sparking interest from several European clubs.<ref>{{cite news|date=5 February 2019|title=Cl\u00e1usula de rescis\u00e3o de Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix pode subir|trans-title=Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix's release clause may go up|url=https://www.abola.pt/Clubes/Noticias/Ver/772041/40|url-status=dead|language=pt|newspaper=[[A Bola]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190205160452/https://abola.pt/Clubes/Noticias/Ver/772041/40/|archive-date=5 February 2019|access-date=14 February 2019}}</ref> A month later, he scored the equaliser in a 2\u20131 away win over Porto in the league.<ref>{{cite news|date=17 March 2019|title=Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix explica festejo de joelhos no Drag\u00e3o|trans-title=Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix explains celebration on his knees at Drag\u00e3o|url=https://maisfutebol.iol.pt/benfica/liga/joao-felix-explica-festejo-de-joelhos-no-dragao|language=pt|work=Maisfutebol|access-date=3 July 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn 11 April 2019, F\u00e9lix scored a hat-trick in a 4\u20132 [[UEFA Europa League]] win over [[Eintracht Frankfurt]]. In doing so, he became the youngest ever player (aged 19 years and 152 days) to score a hat-trick in the competition, breaking [[Marko Pjaca]]'s record by 67 days.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/47903362|title=Europa League Roundup: Joao Felix hat-trick; English refs award three pens and a red|work=[[BBC Sport]]|date=11 April 2019|access-date=12 April 2019}}</ref> F\u00e9lix finished his first season with 20 goals for his team, including one on the final day of the league campaign, in a 4\u20131 win over [[C.D. Santa Clara|Santa Clara]] to seal the title;<ref>{{cite news|title=Benfica-Santa Clara: Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix chega aos 20 golos pela equipa principal|trans-title=Benfica-Santa Clara: Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix reaches 20 goals for the first team|url=https://www.ojogo.pt/futebol/1a-liga/benfica/noticias/interior/benfica-santa-clara-joao-felix-chega-aos-20-golos-pela-equipa-principal-10914534.html|access-date=27 May 2019|newspaper=O Jogo|date=18 May 2019|language=pt}}</ref> his 15 league goals put him joint-fourth for the season.<ref>{{cite news|title=Goleadores: Seferovi\u0107 \u00e9 o melhor marcador da Liga|trans-title=Goalscorers: Haris Seferovi\u0107 is the top scorer in the League|url=https://maisfutebol.iol.pt/benfica/campeao/goleadores-seferovic-e-o-melhor-marcador-da-liga|access-date=27 May 2019|work=Maisfutebol|date=18 May 2019|language=pt}}</ref> Across Europe's seven best leagues, he ranked second among teenagers for goals and assists, behind [[Kai Havertz]] and [[Jadon Sancho]], respectively.<ref name=\"davis\"/>\n\n===Atl\u00e9tico Madrid===\nOn 3 July 2019, F\u00e9lix signed a seven-year contract with Spanish club [[Atl\u00e9tico Madrid]] for a transfer fee of \u20ac126&nbsp;million (\u00a3113&nbsp;million), the [[List of most expensive association football transfers|third highest ever paid in football]]<ref>{{cite news|date=3 July 2019|title=Atl\u00e9tico Madrid sign Benfica teenager Jo\u00e3o Felix for fee of \u20ac126m|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2019/jul/03/atletico-madrid-sign-benfica-teenager-joao-felix-for-fee-of-126m|newspaper=[[The Guardian]]|agency=[[Reuters]]|access-date=17 July 2019}}</ref> (Benfica's biggest transfer and Atl\u00e9tico's most expensive signing) as well as the second highest for a teenager (after [[Kylian Mbapp\u00e9]]), with the [[La Liga]] club initially paying \u20ac30&nbsp;million and the rest \u20ac96&nbsp;million via [[wiktionary:installment|installment]]s, thus surpassing F\u00e9lix's \u20ac120&nbsp;million [[release clause]], and with Benfica paying \u20ac12&nbsp;million in mediation services.<ref>{{cite news|date=3 July 2019|title=Comunicado \u00e0 CMVM|trans-title=Announcement to CMVM|url=https://www.slbenfica.pt/pt-pt/agora/noticias/2019/07/03/futebol-benfica-comunicado-cmvm-joao-felix-atletico-de-madrid|language=pt|publisher=S.L. Benfica|access-date=3 July 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Garcia|first=Adriana|date=3 July 2019|title=Atletico pay \u20ac126m to sign 'New Ronaldo' Felix|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/soccer-transfers/story/3877518/atletico-pay-126m-to-sign-new-ronaldo-felix|publisher=[[ESPN]]|access-date=3 July 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/48859847|title=Joao Felix: Atletico Madrid sign forward from Benfica for \u00a3113m|work=BBC Sport|date=3 July 2019|access-date=4 July 2019}}</ref> Upon his arrival to the club he was handed the number 7 shirt, previously worn by [[Antoine Griezmann]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix apresentado em direto pelo Atl\u00e9tico de Madrid|url=https://www.impala.pt/desporto/joao-felix-atletico-madrid/|access-date=8 July 2019|work=Impala|date=8 July 2019|language=pt}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix no At. Madrid por sete temporadas|url=https://www.dn.pt/desportos/interior/oficial-joao-felix-no-atletico-de-madrid-11056397.html|work=Di\u00e1rio de Not\u00edcias|date=8 July 2019|language=pt}}</ref>\n\n[[File:20191002SR.jpg|thumb|upright|F\u00e9lix playing for [[Atl\u00e9tico Madrid]] in a away [[2019\u201320 UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] match against [[Lokomotiv Moscow]].]]\nF\u00e9lix made his competitive debut on 19 August, in a 1\u20130 victory over [[Getafe CF|Getafe]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.marca.com/en/football/spanish-football/cronica/2019/08/19/5d59d500268e3e1b448b45c2.html|title=Atletico Madrid start the season in typical fashion|website=MARCA|date=19 August 2019}}</ref> Despite not scoring a goal, he managed to get a penalty for Atl\u00e9tico after being fouled, a penalty that [[\u00c1lvaro Morata]] failed to convert.<ref>{{cite news|title=A jogada de Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix de que todos falam|url=https://pt.besoccer.com/noticia/a-jogada-de-joao-felix-de-que-todos-falam-581512|work=BeSoccer|date=19 August 2019|language=pt}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|date=19 August 2019|title=S\u00f3 com pen\u00e1lti o Getafe travou jogada genial de F\u00e9lix|url=https://www.abola.pt/nnh/Noticias/Ver/802008|url-status=live|language=pt|newspaper=A Bola|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190818235517/https://www.abola.pt/nnh/Noticias/Ver/802008|archive-date=18 August 2018|access-date=18 August 2019}}</ref> On 25 August, F\u00e9lix provided an assist for [[Vitolo (footballer, born 1989)|Vitolo]] in a 1\u20130 away win over against [[CD Legan\u00e9s]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://observador.pt/2019/08/25/ainda-sem-golos-mas-com-assistencia-atl-madrid-bate-leganes-com-joao-felix-a-assistir-para-o-golo-da-vitoria/ |title=Ainda sem golos mas com assist\u00eancia: Atl. Madrid bate Legan\u00e9s com Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix a assistir para o golo da vit\u00f3ria|website=Observador|date=23 August 2019 |accessdate=23 August 2019}}</ref> He scored his first La Liga goal on 1 September, in a 3\u20132 victory over [[SD Eibar|Eibar]]; he was later substituted in the 84th minute by [[Thomas Partey]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://trivela.com.br/joao-felix-fez-seu-primeiro-gol-oficial-pelo-atletico-e-deu-inicio-a-virada-contra-o-eibar/|title=Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix fez seu primeiro gol oficial pelo Atl\u00e9tico e deu in\u00edcio \u00e0 virada contra o Eibar|website=Trivela|date=1 September 2019|last=Bonsanti|first=Bruno}}</ref> On 1 October, F\u00e9lix scored his first [[2019\u201320 UEFA Champions League|UEFA Champions League]] goal and set up another goal in a 2-1 away victory against [[Lokomotiv Moscow]], becoming in the process, the youngest goalscorer for Atletico Madrid in this competition at 19 years old.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sol.sapo.pt/artigo/672943/joao-felix-estreia-se-a-marcar-na-liga-dos-campeoes-e-faz-historia-ao-quebrar-recorde-video|title=Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix estreia-se a marcar na Liga dos Campe\u00f5es e faz hist\u00f3ria ao quebrar recorde|website=Jornal SOL|date=1 October 2019}}</ref> On 19 October, F\u00e9lix suffered an ankle injury against [[Valencia CF|Valencia]], after a rash challenge by [[Dani Parejo]], leading his team to be down with 10-men, since his coach [[Diego Simeone]] had made all the substitutions.<ref>{{cite_web|url=https://www.cmjornal.pt/desporto/futebol/detalhe/joao-felix-lesionou-se-com-gravidade-no-jogo-contra-o-valencia|title=Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix lesionou-se com gravidade no jogo contra o valencia|accessdate=19 October 2019|website=Correio da Manh\u00e3}}</ref> Initially, Diego Simeone thought his injury wasn't serious, until a Atletico Madrid's medical team revealed that the ankle injury could be a serious injury, leading him to be sidelined for one month.<ref>{{cite_web|url=https://www.cmjornal.pt/desporto/futebol/detalhe/saiba-qual-o-tempo-de-paragem-de-joao-felix-apos-lesao|title=Saiba qual o tempo de paragem de Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix ap\u00f3s les\u00e3o|accessdate=20 October 2019|website=Correio da Manh\u00e3}}</ref> He made his return on 23 November in a 1-1 away draw against [[Granada CF]].<ref>{{cite_web|url=https://www.laliga.com/en-GB/match/temporada-2019-2020-laliga-santander-granada-cf-atletico-de-madrid-14|title=Atl\u00e9tico de Madrid vs. Granada|accessdate=23 November 2019|website=La Liga}}</ref> During this time, F\u00e9lix was nominated as one amongst 30 candidates for [[2019 Ballon d'Or|2019]] [[Ballon d'Or]].<ref>{{cite_web|url=https://www.theportugalnews.com/news/ronaldo-felix-and-silva-nominated-for-ballon-dor/51730|title=Ronaldo, F\u00e9lix and Silva nominated for Ballon d\u00b4Or|accessdate=25 October 2019|website=The Portugal News}}</ref> On 27 November, he became the second Portuguese player, after [[Renato Sanches]], to win the [[Golden Boy Award|Golden Boy award]] for best European player under the age of 21, ahead of [[Borussia Dortmund]]'s [[Jadon Sancho]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/50570064|title=Golden Boy award: Joao Felix named best under-21 player in Europe|date=27 November 2019|website=BBC Sport}}</ref> In December, F\u00e9lix ended 28th place in the voting polls for the [[2019 Ballon d'Or]].<ref>{{cite_web|url=https://www.manisteenews.com/sports/article/US-soccer-star-Rapinoe-wins-Ballon-d-Or-14876298.php|title=Megan Rapinoe, Lionel Messi win Ballon d\u2019Or awards|accessdate=2 December 2019|website=News Manistee Advocate|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191203150930/https://www.manisteenews.com/sports/article/US-soccer-star-Rapinoe-wins-Ballon-d-Or-14876298.php|archive-date=3 December 2019|url-status=dead}}</ref> Over the following months, F\u00e9lix started to have difficulties on adapting to Diego Simeone's playing style, with Simeone trying to find his ideal position either as a [[Midfielder#Winger|right winger]] or [[second striker]], and also the fact that forwards press a lot, ended up wearing him out, while also being unable to create scoring chances with the ball off his feet,<ref>{{cite_web|url=https://www.noticiasaominuto.com/desporto/1408480/joao-felix-nao-esta-feliz-no-atletico-o-sistema-de-simeone-desgasta-o|title=\"Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix n\u00e3o est\u00e1 feliz no Atl\u00e9tico. O sistema de Simeone desgasta-o\"|accessdate=2 February 2020|website=Sapo Desporto}}</ref> leading Spanish newspaper ''[[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]]'' to name him one of the disappointing transfers of the season.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sol.sapo.pt/artigo/682102/joao-felix-entre-as-desilusoes-da-la-liga|title=Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix entre as desilus\u00f5es da La Liga|website=Jornal SOL|date=6 January 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 9 January 2020, F\u00e9lix made his debut in the [[2019\u201320 Supercopa de Espa\u00f1a|Supercopa de Espa\u00f1a]], providing an assist for [[Koke (footballer, born 1992)|Koke]] in a 3-2 victory against [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]] in the semifinal.<ref>{{cite_web|url=https://www.laliga.com/en-GB/match/temporada-2019-2020-supercopa-de-espana-fc-barcelona-atletico-de-madrid-1|title=Supercopa de Espa\u00f1a semifinal|accessdate=9 January 2020|website=La Liga}}</ref> During the match, F\u00e9lix was involved in a altercation with [[Jordi Alba]] and his teammates [[Lionel Messi]] and [[Luis Suarez]].<ref>{{cite_web|url=https://www.dn.pt/desportos/joao-felix-e-messi-pegados-no-intervalo-do-barcelona-at-madrid-11689592.html|title=Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix e Messi pegados no intervalo do Barcelona-At. Madrid|accessdate=9 January 2020|website=Di\u00e1rio de Not\u00edcias}}</ref> On 12 January, Atletico Madrid lost to their [[Madrid Derby|rivals]] [[Real Madrid]] 4\u20131 on penalties in the final.<ref>{{cite_web|url=https://www.laliga.com/en-GB/match/temporada-2019-2020-supercopa-de-espana-real-madrid-atletico-de-madrid-2|title=Supercopa de Espa\u00f1a final|accessdate=12 January 2020|website=La Liga}}</ref> On 23 January, F\u00e9lix made his [[2019\u201320 Copa del Rey|Copa del Rey]] debut in the Round of 32, provind an assist for [[\u00c1ngel Correa]] in a 2-1 loss against [[Cultural y Deportiva Leonesa|Cultural Leonesa]].<ref>{{cite_web|url=https://www.laliga.com/en-GB/match/temporada-2019-2020-copa-del-rey-cultural-leonesa-atletico-de-madrid-3|title=Copa del Rey round of 32|accessdate=23 January 2020|website=La Liga}}</ref> Three days later, F\u00e9lix suffered a second injury on his leg in a 0-0 home draw against CD Legan\u00e9s, sidelining him again for a month, leading him to miss to Atletico Madrid's next three league matches, which included the second [[Madrid Derby]] of the season and Atletico Madrid's first leg of their round of 16 Champions League against [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.abola.pt/nnh/2020-01-29/atletico-madrid-joao-felix-lesiona-se-e-esta-em-duvida-para-o-derbi/826785|title=JO\u00c3O F\u00c9LIX LESIONA-SE E EST\u00c1 EM D\u00daVIDA PARA O D\u00c9RBI|website=A Bola|date=26 January 2020}}</ref> He made his return on 23 February, replacing Vitolo in the 57th minute, scoring the third goal in a 3-1 home victory against [[Villarreal CF|Villarreal]].<ref>{{cite_web|url=https://www.laliga.com/en-GB/match/temporada-2019-2020-laliga-santander-atletico-de-madrid-villarreal-cf-25|accessdate=23 February 2020|title=Atletico Madrid vs Villarreal|website=La Liga}}</ref> On 11 March 2020, during [[Overtime (sports)|extra time]] of the [[2019\u201320 UEFA Champions League|Champions League round-of-16 tie]] away to [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]] in the second leg, F\u00e9lix provided an assist for [[Marcos Llorente]] in an eventual 3\u20132 win and qualification to the quarterfinals of the Champions League.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/sport/football/liverpool-vs-atletico-madrid-live-score-champions-league-result-a4385036.html?amp|title=Liverpool crash out of Champions League to Atletico Madrid \u2013 LIVE! Latest news and result reaction|newspaper=[[Evening Standard]]|last=Doyle|first=Tom|date=11 March 2020|accessdate=11 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\n===Youth===\nOn 14 June 2017, F\u00e9lix began his international career with [[Portugal national under-18 football team|Portugal's under-18 team]], debuting against [[Norway national under-18 football team|Norway]], replacing [[Elves Bald\u00e9]] in the 58th minute. In this friendly match, F\u00e9lix scored two goals in a 3\u20130 victory in Lisbon. On 10 October 2017, F\u00e9lix debuted for [[Portugal national under-21 football team|Portugal's under-21 team]] for the qualification of the [[2019 UEFA European Under-21 Championship]], in a 3\u20131 defeat against [[Bosnia and Herzegovina national under-21 football team|Bosnia and Herzegovina]], replacing [[Xadas]] in the 56th minute.<ref>{{cite web|title=UEFA Bosnia and Herzegovina vs Portugal qualification for the 2019 UEFA European Under-21 Championship debut|url=https://pt.uefa.com/under21/season=2019/matches/round=2000803/match=2022501/|access-date=3 September 2019|website=[[UEFA]]|date=10 October 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=B\u00f3snia-Portugal, 3\u20131: Primeira derrota em apuramentos em 6 anos|url=https://www.record.pt/internacional/competicoes-de-selecoes/europeu-sub-21/detalhe/sub-21-bosnia-portugal-em-direto|access-date=3 September 2019|newspaper=Record|date=10 October 2017}}</ref>\n\nOn 15 January 2018, F\u00e9lix debuted for [[Portugal national under-19 football team|Portugal's under-19 team]] as a 27th minute substitute for an injured Jorge Teixeira in a 2\u20131 win over [[Turkey national under-19 football team|Turkey]]. On 23 March 2018, F\u00e9lix scored his first international goal for Portugal's under-21 team in a 7\u20130 thrashing of [[Liechtenstein national under-21 football team|Liechtenstein]].<ref>{{cite news|title=UEFA Liechtenstein vs Portugal qualification for the 2019 UEFA European Under-21 Championship debut|url=https://pt.uefa.com/under21/season=2019/matches/round=2000803/match=2022482/|access-date=3 September 2019|publisher=UEFA|date=23 March 2018}}</ref> In the end of the qualification process, he had scored four goals, helping guide Portugal to the [[2019 UEFA European Under-21 Championship qualification play-offs|play-offs]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Brilho de uma gera\u00e7\u00e3o deu para o playoff, para j\u00e1|url=https://www.zerozero.pt/news.php?id=233064|access-date=3 September 2019|work=zerozero|date=23 March 2018}}</ref> In the first leg of the play-offs, Portugal faced [[Poland national under-21 football team|Poland]] in a 1\u20130 away victory, but eventually lost in the second leg in a 3\u20131 home defeat, failing to qualify for the tournament.<ref>{{cite news|title=Play-offs 1st leg|url=https://pt.uefa.com/under21/season=2019/matches/round=2000804/match=2025681/|access-date=3 September 2019|publisher=UEFA|date=16 November 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Play-offs 2nd leg|url=https://pt.uefa.com/under21/season=2019/matches/round=2000804/match=2025682/|access-date=3 September 2019|publisher=UEFA|date=20 November 2018}}</ref>\n\nDuring his international youth career, F\u00e9lix would go on to represent the under-18, under-19 and under-21 teams, amassing 14 youth caps and scoring 6 goals overall.{{citation needed|date=March 2020}}\n\n===Senior===\nOn 15 March 2019, manager [[Fernando Santos (Portuguese footballer)|Fernando Santos]] called up F\u00e9lix to the [[Portugal national football team|senior team]] for the first time, ahead of the opening [[UEFA Euro 2020 qualifying]] matches.<ref>{{cite news|date=15 March 2019|title=Eagles called up to the national team|url=https://www.slbenfica.pt/en-us/agora/noticias/2018-2019/03/15/futebol-jogadores-benfica-convocados-selecao-portugal-jogos-ucrania-e-servia-apuramento-europeu|publisher=S.L. Benfica|access-date=5 July 2019}}</ref> During training with the national squad, F\u00e9lix injured his foot and thus missed Portugal's match against [[Serbia national football team|Serbia]] on 25 March.<ref>{{cite news|last=Barbosa|first=Nuno|date=25 March 2019|title=UEFA deixa lesionado Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix de fora do Portugal\u2013S\u00e9rvia|trans-title=UEFA leaves injured Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix out of Portugal\u2013Serbia|url=https://www.jn.pt/desporto/interior/uefa-deixa-lesionado-joao-felix-de-fora-do-portugal-servia-10721509.html|language=pt|newspaper=[[Jornal de Not\u00edcias]]|access-date=5 July 2019}}</ref>\n\nF\u00e9lix was also selected for the [[2019 UEFA Nations League Finals]] squad on home soil.<ref>{{cite news|title=Portugal name Cristiano Ronaldo and Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix in Nations League squad|url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/13954/11727023/portugal-name-cristiano-ronaldo-and-joao-felix-in-nations-league-squad|access-date=27 May 2019|work=[[Sky Sports]]|date=24 May 2019}}</ref> He made his international debut for the senior team on 5 June against [[Switzerland national football team|Switzerland]] in the semi-finals, where he was substituted in the 71st minute of a 3\u20131 win.<ref>{{cite news|title=Joao Felix is rated at \u00a3106m but he struggled on his Portugal debut|url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/13954/11735790/joao-felix-is-rated-at-106m-but-he-struggled-on-his-portugal-debut|access-date=6 June 2019|work=Sky Sports|date=6 June 2019}}</ref> Four days later, Portugal defeated [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands]] 1\u20130 in the tournament's final.<ref>{{cite news|last=Law|first=Matt|title=Result: Goncalo Guedes scores winner as Portugal land UEFA Nations League title|url=https://www.sportsmole.co.uk/football/portugal/uefa-nations-league/result/result-guedes-scores-winner-as-portugal-land-nations-league-title_361579.html|access-date=9 June 2019|work=Sports Mole|date=5 July 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Style of play==\nConsidered by Benfica to be one of the most promising players to have emerged from their [[S.L. Benfica Juniors|youth ranks]], as well as regarded considered by pundits as one of the most talented young players in world football,<ref name=\"en.as.com\"/><ref name=\"paraeles\"/> F\u00e9lix is a highly skilful and technical player,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.cnn.com/2019/04/17/sport/joao-felix-benfica-spt-intl/index.html |title=Joao Felix: The Benfica teen who is a 'star already' |publisher=CNN |last1=Macguire |first1=Eoghan |date=7 May 2019 |accessdate=11 April 2020 }}</ref> who is capable of playing in several offensive positions, due to his versatility; throughout his career, he has been deployed as a [[Striker (association football)|striker]], as a [[Forward (association football)#Second striker|second striker]], or even as a [[Midfielder#Winger|winger]], although his primary position is that of an [[attacking midfielder]].<ref name=\"en.as.com\"/><ref>{{cite news|url=https://observador.pt/2018/08/25/joao-felix-o-miudo-dos-pestinhas-que-saiu-do-fc-porto-por-ser-magricelas-e-esta-a-ganhar-cabedal-no-benfica/|title=Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix, o mi\u00fado dos Pestinhas que saiu do FC Porto por ser magricelas e est\u00e1 a ganhar cabedal no Benfica|trans-title=Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix, the Pestinhas kid who left FC Porto for being scrawny and is gaining muscle at Benfica|newspaper=Observador|language=pt|last=Roseiro|first=Bruno|date=25 August 2018||access-date=17 January 2019}}</ref> With Benfica, F\u00e9lix usually played as a second striker in a [[Formation (association football)#4\u20134\u20132|4\u20134\u20132 formation]], where he was tasked with linking up the midfield with the attack, as well as creating opportunities for the team's main striker, while also being given the freedom to make runs into the box and score goals himself.<ref name=\"en.as.com\"/><ref name=\"davis\"/> With Atl\u00e9tico Madrid, he has occasionally played in a similar role, but has often been deployed as a right winger in the team's 4\u20134\u20132 formation.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.marca.com/en/football/spanish-football/2020/02/25/5e5510c222601d46538b459b.html |title=Joao Felix is finally seeing the light |publisher=Marca |last1=Medina |first1=David G. |date=25 February 2020 |accessdate=11 April 2020 }}</ref> A quick and intelligent player, with an eye for goal, his primary traits are his speed, creativity, finishing, touch on the ball, and [[Dribbling#Association football|dribbling]] skills, as well as his vision and precise passing.<ref name=\"en.as.com\"/><ref name=DiarioNoticias></ref>{{cite web |url=https://bleacherreport.com/articles/2858128-matthijs-de-ligt-joao-felix-jadon-sancho-on-20-man-2019-golden-boy-shortlist |title=Matthijs de Ligt, Joao Felix, Jadon Sancho on 20-Man 2019 Golden Boy Shortlist |publisher=Bleacher Report |last1=Jones |first1=Matt |date=15 October 2019 |accessdate=8 March 2020 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://ca.sports.yahoo.com/news/atletico-madrids-joao-felix-is-the-best-signing-of-the-summer-183220159.html |title=Atletico Madrid's Joao Felix is the best signing of the summer |publisher=Yahoo Sports |last1=Bailey |first1=Ryan |date=29 July 2019 |accessdate=8 March 2020 }}</ref> His playing style has led him to be compared to Brazilian former [[playmaker]] [[Kak\u00e1]] and former Benfica players [[Rui Costa]] and [[Jo\u00e3o Pinto]].<ref name=\"en.as.com\"/><ref name=\"paraeles\"/>\n\n==Personal life==\nF\u00e9lix's parents, Carlos (father) and Carla (mother), are both teachers. He has a younger brother, Hugo, who plays for Benfica youth ranks.<ref name=lb/> Growing up, F\u00e9lix's idols were Kak\u00e1 and Rui Costa, the latter a player he looked to emulate.<ref>{{cite news|title=Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix fala de tudo. As praxes, os \u00eddolos, a rela\u00e7\u00e3o com Vieira, o n.\u00ba 10 e a Bola de Ouro|trans-title=Jo\u00e3o Felix talks about everything. The pranks, the idols, the relationship with Vieira, the number 10 and the Golden Ball|url=https://www.dn.pt/desportos/interior/joao-felix-fala-de-tudo-as-praxes-os-idolos-a-relacao-com-vieira-o-n10-e-a-bola-de-ouro-10938513.html|newspaper=Di\u00e1rio de Not\u00edcias|date=24 May 2019|language=pt}}</ref> F\u00e9lix is in a relationship with Portuguese actress Margarida Corceiro, with the couple being discrete about their relationship at first, but later Corceiro publicly revealed it.<ref>{{cite news|title=Margarida Corceiro conta como come\u00e7ou a namorar com Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix|url=https://selfie.iol.pt/voce-na-tv/manuel-luis-goucha/margarida-corceiro-conta-como-comecou-a-namorar-com-joao-felix|date=7 February 2020|language=pt}}</ref>\n\nOn April 14, 2020, F\u00e9lix made a donation of equipment to a crowdfunding campaign to an hospital in his hometown in [[Viseu]] to help with the struggle of the [[COVID-19 pandemic|Coronavirus (COVID-19) pandemic]].<ref>vidas.pt/a-ferver/detalhe/joao-felix-mostra-se-solidario-e-faz-donativo-a-hospital</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n===Club===\n{{updated|match played 11 March 2020}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|+ Appearances and goals by club, season and competition\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!colspan=\"3\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|National Cup{{efn|Includes [[Ta\u00e7a de Portugal]], [[Copa del Rey]]}}\n!colspan=\"2\"|League Cup{{efn|Includes [[Ta\u00e7a da Liga]]}}\n!colspan=\"2\"|Europe\n!colspan=\"2\"|Other\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n!Division!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\"|[[S.L. Benfica B|Benfica B]]\n|[[2016\u201317 LigaPro|2016\u201317]]<ref name=\"Soccerway\"/>\n|[[LigaPro]]\n|13||3||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||13||3\n|-\n|[[2017\u201318 LigaPro|2017\u201318]]<ref name=\"Soccerway\"/>\n|LigaPro\n|17||4||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||17||4\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n!30||7||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||30||7\n|-\n|[[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]]\n|[[2018\u201319 S.L. Benfica season|2018\u201319]]<ref name=\"Soccerway\"/><ref>For Ta\u00e7a de Portugal third round: {{cite news|url=https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/taca-de-portugal/detalhe/sertanense-benfica-em-direto|title=Sertanense-Benfica, 0\u20133|newspaper=Record|date=18 October 2018|access-date=2 March 2020|language=Portuguese}}</ref>\n|[[Primeira Liga]]\n|26||15||6||1||2||1||9{{efn|Three appearances in [[UEFA Champions League]], six appearances and three goals in [[UEFA Europa League]]}}||3||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||43||20\n|-\n|[[Atl\u00e9tico Madrid]]\n|[[2019\u201320 Atl\u00e9tico Madrid season|2019\u201320]]<ref name=\"Soccerway\">{{cite web|url=https://uk.soccerway.com/players/joao-felix--sequeira/459986/|title=Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix: Summary|website=Soccerway|publisher=Perform Group|access-date=2 March 2020}}</ref>\n|[[La Liga]]\n|20||4||1||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||5{{efn|Appearances in UEFA Champions League}}||2||2{{efn|Appearances in [[Supercopa de Espa\u00f1a]]}}||0||28||6\n|-\n!colspan=\"3\"|Career total\n!76||26||7||1||2||1||14||5||2||0||101||33\n|}\n\n{{notelist}}\n\n===International===\n{{updated|match played 14 October 2019}}<ref>{{NFT player |pid=74472 |name=Jo\u00e3o F\u00e9lix |accessdate=2 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|+ Appearances and goals by national team and year\n|-\n!National team!!Year!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|[[Portugal national football team|Portugal]]\n|2019||5||0\n|-\n!colspan=2|Total||5||0\n|}\n\n==Honours==\n'''Benfica'''\n*[[Primeira Liga]]: [[2018\u201319 Primeira Liga|2018\u201319]]<ref name=\"Soccerway\"/>\n*[[Campeonato Nacional de Juniores]]: 2017